</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35757FFB3FEB55F2DFDF82434" authority="Simon, 1901" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[298,591,1381,1405]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigris">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725757FFB3FEB55F2DFE712434" box="[298,454,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">Scoturius tigris</emphasis>
Simon, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB639605757FFB3FF085FE3FDBA2733" blockId="16.[151,1437,1451,1658]" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725757FFB3FF085FE3FEC1248C" bold="true" box="[151,374,1451,1477]" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844915757FFB3FE1D5FE3FD86248C" author="Galiano, M. E." box="[386,561,1451,1477]" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" pagination="285 - 301" refId="ref17400" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1988) Revision de los generos del grupo Hurieae (Araneae, Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology, 15, 285 - 301." type="journal article" year="1988">Galiano (1988)</bibRefCitation>
proposed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35757FFB3FD795FE3FCE7248C" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[742,848,1451,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725757FFB3FD795FE3FCE7248C" box="[742,848,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">Scoturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other huriine genera in having three retrolateral tibial apophysis. However, after comparisons of male palp across the tribe, we proposed a new interpretation, meaning that the two more dorsal branches may be developments of two RTA lobes (see discussion below). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35757FFB3FEC35C5FFE712778" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[348,454,1559,1585]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725757FFB3FEC35C5FFE712778" box="[348,454,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">Scoturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35757FFB3FD065C50FBA6277B" authority="Ruiz &amp; Maddison, 2015" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2015" box="[665,1041,1559,1586]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Urupuyu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725757FFB3FD065C50FD4A2778" box="[665,765,1560,1585]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">Urupuyu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844915757FFB3FC9C5C5FFBA6277B" author="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Maddison, W. P." box="[771,1041,1559,1586]" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" pagination="251 - 279" refId="ref18154" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Maddison, W. P. (2015) The new Andean jumping spider genus Urupuyu and its placement within a revised classification of the Amycoida (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa, 4040 (3), 251 - 279 https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4040.3.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Ruiz &amp; Maddison, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having the RTA with two lobes. However, males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35757FFB3FEEE5C73FE6C271C" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[369,475,1595,1621]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725757FFB3FEEE5C73FE6C271C" box="[369,475,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">Scoturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35757FFB3FD5C5C74FC90271C" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2015" box="[707,807,1596,1621]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Urupuyu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725757FFB3FD5C5C74FC90271C" box="[707,807,1596,1621]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="447">Urupuyu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the two lobes of RTA finger-shaped and independent (lobes much shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35757FFB3FE065C28FE4A2730" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2015" box="[409,509,1632,1657]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Urupuyu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
